<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<Patch>

    <!--
        MEDIEVAL OVERHAUL COMPATIBILITY

        Problem:
          MO's "Wood Chain" system replaces tree-drop WoodLog with DankPyon_RawWood (raw logs).
          WoodLog is renamed "wood plank" (the refined form) and is now ONLY obtainable by
          processing raw logs at a Trestle — which requires the DankPyon_Lumber research to build.

          Our SurvivalToolBasic accepts [Woody, Stony, Metallic] stuff. Woody = WoodLog = "wood plank"
          = behind a research gate. On day 1 you have raw logs but can't make any tools from them,
          creating a softlock where you can't bootstrap research without tools and can't get tools
          without refined materials.

          Note: MO's woodChain patch *attempts* to add DankPyon_RawWood to Neolithic+Woody ThingDefs,
          but targeting abstract ThingDefs across mods via XML patch can be unreliable depending on
          load order and inheritance resolution timing. Our explicit patch is the safe guarantee.

        Fix:
          Add DankPyon_RawWood as an accepted stuff for SurvivalToolBasic. Raw logs can now be used
          directly to craft wooden tools at the CraftingSpot — no Trestle or research gate needed.
          Behavior is identical when MO is not loaded (PatchOperationFindMod is a no-op).
    -->

    <!-- Add raw logs as a valid crafting material for all basic tools -->
    <Operation Class="PatchOperationFindMod">
        <mods>
            <li>Medieval Overhaul</li>
        </mods>
        <match Class="PatchOperationAdd">
            <xpath>Defs/ThingDef[@Name="SurvivalToolBasic"]/stuffCategories</xpath>
            <value>
                <li>DankPyon_RawWood</li>
            </value>
        </match>
    </Operation>

    <!--
        Add MO's Anvil as a recipe station for all SurvivalToolBasic tools.
        The Anvil is MO's core smithing bench (no research needed, costs Metallic stuff + skill 4).
        Without this, MO players must use the vanilla CraftingSpot (ground spot) or ElectricSmithy
        with no medieval-appropriate intermediate option.
    -->
    <Operation Class="PatchOperationFindMod">
        <mods>
            <li>Medieval Overhaul</li>
        </mods>
        <match Class="PatchOperationAdd">
            <xpath>Defs/ThingDef[@Name="SurvivalToolBasic"]/recipeMaker/recipeUsers</xpath>
            <value>
                <li>DankPyon_Anvil</li>
            </value>
        </match>
    </Operation>

</Patch>
